ls that the text was originally influenced by Deuteronomy and the (Deutero)nomistic theology. Later, it came under priestly and Levitical influence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aAltes Testament. 4aEsra (Buch). 4aNehemia (Buch). 4aPentateuch. 4aSchriftgelehrter. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGY TITLES IN ENGLISHz9783110305630oZDB-23-DBL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGYz9783110305654oZDB-23-DBK0 cprintz978311018280440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091562440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110915624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110915624/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBK  aZDB-23-DBL  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014